## 4. Console Extensions

### Extension Label Format
For labels in plugin extension files, use the special format:

```json
{
  "type": "console.navigation/href",
  "properties": {
    "name": "%plugin__kubevirt-plugin~Virtual Machines%",
    "href": "/virtualization/vms"
  }
}
```

### Register in i18n
Add a comment in `src/utils/i18n.ts` for the parser. This is the **only** file where comment-only `// t('...')` patterns are valid -- they tell `i18next-parser` to extract strings that are referenced dynamically elsewhere and cannot be discovered by static analysis:

```typescript
// Console extension strings - these are used in plugin-extensions.ts
// t('plugin__kubevirt-plugin~Virtual Machines')
// t('plugin__kubevirt-plugin~Templates')
// t('plugin__kubevirt-plugin~Catalog')
```

**Note**: This comment-only pattern is exclusively for `src/utils/i18n.ts`. In all other files, `t()` must be a real, executed call (see Section 12).

